\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zlf1723641763139.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zlf1723641763139.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zlf1723641763139.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zlf1723641763139\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Tables are created on the fly, or by using the SQL scripts generated by the Create\n\t\tTable facility. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__section_w3733ab1b5b1_w3734ab1b5_w3735ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\">When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the\n\t\t\t\ttable does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the\n\t\t\t\tapplication model. The table is created in the following way:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__ol_yhc_dgv_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">create table</code> statement is issued. The primary key\n\t\t\t\t\tconstraint is created within table creation.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Indexes are created with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create index</code> statement.</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__section_yvq_hgv_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d768584e71\">Overflow Tables</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__p_d58754e1_d58755e1_d58756e1\">For entities with only fixed length fields the\n\t\t\t\tmaximum record size is 2GB-1. The maximum record size for entities that have\n\t\t\t\tvariable-length fields is 8KB, the rest goes into the overflow table.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__p_d58757e1_d58758e1_d58759e1\">Overflow tables are created on the fly when needed.\n\t\t\t\tAn overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow\n\t\t\t\tinformation from the field that causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow\n\t\t\t\ttable consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix\n\t\t\t\t\t<code class=\"ph codeph\">O</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__note_hmz_3gv_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The overflow mechanism is a\n      technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications.\n      For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rvk1665702925977.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rvk1665702925977.html\" title=\"DBMSs may impose upper limits to the number of fields in a table, the length of a field, and the length of a record. Some DBMSs do not support variable-length fields with a high maximum length. To overcome these limitations, Uniface provides an overflow mechanism, in which data that is represented as a single modeled entity is automatically split into two tables—the base table and an overflow table.\">Overflow Tables</a>. </div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__section_ink_jgv_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d768584e96\">Segmented Field Support</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__p_d58763e1_d58764e1_d58765e1\">Segmented fields, BLOBs, and CLOBs are\n\t\t\t\tsupported.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__section_orb_lgv_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d768584e105\">Limits</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zlf1723641763139__p_d58769e1_d58770e1_d58771e1\">For details about the SQLite limits for records,\n\t\t\t\tindexes, tables, and fields, consult the SQLite documentation.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424453\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8424453\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Table Management on SQLite Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tables are created on the fly, or by using the SQL scripts generated by the Create Table facility. When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model. The table is created in the following way: The create table statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation. Indexes are created with the create index statement. Overflow Tables For entities with only fixed length fields the maximum record size is 2GB-1. The maximum record size for entities that have variable-length fields is 8KB, the rest goes into the overflow table. Overflow tables are created on the fly when needed. An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix O . Note: The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications. For more information, see Overflow Tables . Segmented Field Support Segmented fields, BLOBs, and CLOBs are supported. Limits For details about the SQLite limits for records, indexes, tables, and fields, consult the SQLite documentation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}